verses.text:
John to the seven churches which are in Asia: Grace \add be\add*
unto you, and peace, from him which is, and which was, and which is to
come; and from the seven Spirits which are before his throne;

His head and \add his\add* hairs \add were\add* white like
wool, as white as snow; and his eyes \add were\add* as a flame of
fire;

\wj  And unto the angel of the church of the Laodiceans write;
These things saith the Amen, the faithful and true witness, the beginning
of the creation of God;\wj*

And I beheld, and I heard the voice of many angels round about
the throne and the beasts and the elders: and the number of them was
ten thousand times ten thousand, and thousands of thousands;

And I beheld when he had opened the sixth seal, and, lo, there
was a great earthquake; and the sun became black as sackcloth of
hair, and the moon became as blood;

And the second angel sounded, and as it were a great mountain
burning with fire was cast into the sea: and the third part of the
sea became blood;

And the third angel sounded, and there fell a great star from
heaven, burning as it were a lamp, and it fell upon the third part
of the rivers, and upon the fountains of waters;

And they had breastplates, as it were breastplates of iron;
and the sound of their wings \add was\add* as the sound of chariots
of many horses running to battle.

Saying with a loud voice, Fear God, and give glory to him;
for the hour of his judgment is come: and worship him that made heaven,
and earth, and the sea, and the fountains of waters.

And the voice of harpers, and musicians, and of pipers, and
trumpeters, shall be heard no more at all in thee; and no craftsman,
of whatsoever craft \add he be\add*, shall be found any more in thee;
and the sound of a millstone shall be heard no more at all in thee;

And the foundations of the wall of the city \add were\add*
garnished with all manner of precious stones. The first foundation
\add was\add* jasper; the second, sapphire; the third, a chalcedony;
the fourth, an emerald;

The fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolite;
the eighth, beryl; the ninth, a topaz; the tenth, a chrysoprasus;
the eleventh, a jacinth; the twelfth, an amethyst.
